            "id": "c4eea80185854a58a817e",
            "questionText": "A car traveling at $!$10 \\text{ m/s}$!$ has a braking distance of $!$10 \\text{ m}$!$ and a driver's reaction time of $!$0.8 \\text{ s}$!$. Assuming that the braking force remains constant, calculate the braking distance when the car's speed doubles to $!$20 \\text{ m/s}$!$.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "19f90f58725f49f688159",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the relationship between braking distance and speed when the braking force is constant. Select the correct principle that shows how braking distance depends on the speed.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "22cb5984-2bee-4068-9d45-f3332a62284a"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\text{Braking distance} \\propto v^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\text{Braking distance} \\propto v$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\text{Braking distance} \\propto v^3$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "456984321fe44c97b623a",
                    "stepText": "Great! Now, calculate the ratio of the new speed to the original speed. The car\u2019s speed increases from $!$10 \\text{ m/s}$!$ to $!$20 \\text{ m/s}$!$. What is this ratio?",
