            "id": "6f258597ddbc4a7992271",
            "questionText": "A remote community is considering a new solar farm that is designed to produce the same useful electrical power output as an existing coal-fired thermal power station. The coal plant takes $!$800 \\text{ MJ}$!$ of chemical energy from coal as input over a period of one minute and operates with an energy transfer efficiency of $!$30\\%$!$. The solar farm operates with an efficiency of $!$75\\%$!$. Calculate the total solar energy input required per second for the solar farm in kilowatts.",
